  "response": "Here's the key difference:\n\nAll Android phones are smartphones, but not all smartphones are Android phones:\n\nSmartphone:\n- A mobile device with advanced features\n- Can run applications\n- Has internet connectivity\n- Has a touchscreen interface\n- Can perform computing tasks\n\nAndroid Phone:\n- A smartphone that specifically runs on the Android operating system\n- Developed by Google\n- Uses Android OS as its software platform\n- Examples include Samsung, Google Pixel, OnePlus phones\n\nOther smartphone operating systems include:\n- iOS (Apple iPhones)\n- Windows Phone (discontinued)\n\nSo an Android phone is a type of smartphone, while a smartphone is a broader category of mobile devices.",
